xceptions by subclassing and overriding the migrate method. I need to inspect what subclasses Flyway 8 might offer. Another thought is to add org.flywaydb:flyway-core with a version that matches Boot 2.6.3. But hmm, I’m debating whether to stick with the current version for compatibility. I want to ensure I’m making the best choice here!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Deciding on dependency versions**\\n\\nI need to choose the right dependency version for Flyway. If I add Flyway 8.0.5, I'm wondering if hardcoding the version is okay. I could use `testImplementation 'org.flywaydb:flyway-core:8.0.5'`, but then there's that compatibility issue since it mentions Flyway <7 compatibility. Using version 8 with simulated NoSuchMethod might get tricky. I think I should update to the current Flyway subclass to prevent unresolved issues and avoid extra DataSource, so I'll go with that.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_O0iSVd32DggQMnb8tcicQi2H|fc_0bfd3e2c0b03ddf50169ff9cb05900819595ced17a292afa63", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-autoconfigure/2.6.3/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "    testImplementation 'org.flywaydb:flyway-core:6.5.7'\n", "newText": "    testImplementation 'org.flywaydb:flyway-core:8.0.5'\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 717, "output": 2571, "cacheRead": 18944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22232, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778359436351, "responseId": "resp_0bfd3e2c0b03ddf50169ff9c8d05408195a184e3165a5b5388"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_O0iSVd32DggQMnb8tcicQi2H|fc_0bfd3e2c0b03ddf50169ff9cb05900819595ced17a292afa63", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-autoconfigure/2.6.3/build.gradle."}], "deta